The United States strongly condemns the recent terrorist attacks in Iraq, specifically those carried out by Al Qaida in Iraq against Christians in Baghdad and against innocent civilians throughout the country. The attacks targeted Christians in their homes and churches, as well as pilgrims in the holy cities of Najaf and Karbala. The US offers its condolences to the families of the victims and to all the people of Iraq who are affected by terrorism. The US remains committed to standing with the Iraqi people as they reject violence and resist efforts by Al Qaida in Iraq to create sectarian tension. The US pledges its support to the Government of Iraq as it takes necessary steps to combat terrorism and protect all Iraqi citizens, including vulnerable religious minorities.